===Etymology===
Causative derivation of {{och-l|理|tr=rəʔ}} "envoy ({{w|Zuozhuan|Zuo}})" , "jail-official" ({{w|Guanzi}}), "[[matchmaker|marriage go-between]]" {{zh-ref|(Schuessler 2007)}}; 

Possibly from {{der|zh|aav}}; Schuessler compared {{och-l|[[史]]|tr=-}} & {{och-l|使|tr=srəʔ}} "to send, employ, cause > secretary, scribe" to {{cog|mkh-okm|pre||to send, order, assign, appoint, delegate, use, employ, make}} & {{m|mkh-okm|paṃre||to serve; service, duty; servant, delegate, representative, minister}} with Sino-Tibetan causative *''s-'' corresponding to Khmer causative *''p-''.

Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Unger (1990)}} and {{zh-ref|Starostin & Peiros (1996)}} derived {{och-l|[[史]]}} "scribe, secretary" from {{och-l|理}} "to mark, to draw lines", which is cognate with {{cog|bo|འབྲི||to write, to draw}} yet apparently never meant "to write, to record".

